  <exercise xml:id="empty-15">
    <statement>
      <p>Construct a block of code that changes the first element of <c>vec</c> to a 6,
                    multiplies the third element of <c>vec</c> by 2, and increments the last element
                    of <c>vec</c> by 1 (in that order).  This should work no matter what <c>vec</c> is.</p>
    </statement>
    <program interactive="activecode" line-numbers="yes" xml:id="vectors_p1_ac_q_editor">
      <input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;
// YOUR CODE HERE
        ]]></input>
    </program>
    <solution>


    
                Below is one way to construct the code.

    
    <program xml:id="vectors_p1_ac_a_editor" line-numbers="yes"><input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    vector<int> vec;
    vec.assign(1,10);
    vec[0] = 6;
    vec[2] = vec[2] * 2;
    int last = vec.size() - 1;
    vec[last]++;
}
        ]]></input></program>

            

